&lt;h2 id=&quot;user-configuration&quot;&gt;User configuration&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I haven’t documented or stored all of this to my dotfiles repositories yet. Come back later? :)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;installed-ports&quot;&gt;Installed ports&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following is a list of packages that I usually install pretty quickly after setting up a new system:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;terminal-and-shell-stuff&quot;&gt;Terminal and shell stuff&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;pv (pipe viewer)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rxvt-unicode (terminal)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;scrot (screen capture)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;sudo&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the_silver_searcher (grep replacement for vim)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;zsh (shell)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;development&quot;&gt;Development&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;neovim (from source)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;autotools&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;clang38&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cmake&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;gmake (BSD-make is sadly not very supported)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;desktop-environment&quot;&gt;Desktop environment&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;dmenu (app launcher for i3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;feh (background manager)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;firefox&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git-gui&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;i3-gaps (from source)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;keepass (password manager)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;slim (graphical login)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’m an absolute FreeBSD noob, so some of the stuff listed here is probably suboptimal. Feel free to
